Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: pythtb
Version: 1.8.0
Summary: Simple solver for tight binding models for use in condensed matter physics and materials science.
Home-page: http://www.physics.rutgers.edu/pythtb
Download-URL: http://www.physics.rutgers.edu/pythtb
Author: Sinisa Coh and David Vanderbilt
Author-email: sinisacoh@gmail.com
License: gpl-3.0
Keywords: tight binding,solid state physics,condensed matter physics,materials science
Platform: UNIX
Platform: MAC OS X
Platform: Windows

The tight binding method is an approximate approach for solving for the electronic wave functions for electrons in solids assuming a basis of localized atomic-like orbitals.

